sequenceDiagram
    participant B as Browser
    participant OS as OS/Cache
    participant DNS as DNS Resolver
    participant G as Gateway/Router
    participant BN as Internet Backbone
    participant WS as Web Server

    Note over B, WS: 1. DNS Lookup Phase
    B->>OS: Look up Domain Name (example.com)
    OS-->>B: IP Not Found
    B->>DNS: Recursive Query for IP
    DNS->>DNS: Query Root/TLD Servers
    DNS-->>B: Return IP Address (93.184.216.34)

    Note over B, WS: 2. Connection & Request Phase
    B->>G: TCP SYN (Request Connection)
    G->>BN: Route to Server
    BN->>WS: Forward Packet
    WS-->>BN: TCP SYN-ACK
    BN-->>G: Forwarded
    G-->>B: TCP ACK (Connection Established)

    Note over B, WS: 3. HTTP Exchange Phase
    B->>WS: HTTP GET Request
    WS->>WS: Process Request
    WS-->>B: HTTP 200 OK & Content (HTML)
    B->>B: Render Page
